{"title":"Holy word","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Holy_word","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.30](/0.30 \"0.30\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n**Holy word** is a damaging effect. When used against [undead](/Undead \"Undead\") or [demonic](/Demonic \"Demonic\") monsters, it deals `3d15 + (1d<pow> - 1) / 5`[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1) AC-ignoring damage and inflicts the [daze](/Daze \"Daze\") status for 10-19 turns.[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2)[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3) When used against undead or [demonspawn](/Demonspawn \"Demonspawn\") players, it halves HP instead. Unlike [torment](/Torment \"Torment\"), this can kill you at 1 HP. Otherwise, it does nothing.\n\nHoly word is a divine-only effect. It can be invoked from [The Shining One](/The_Shining_One \"The Shining One\")'s weapon blessing and [Zin](/Zin \"Zin\")'s Recite. [Nemelex](/Nemelex \"Nemelex\") will use holy word exclusively on the player as [punishment](/Torment_card \"Torment card\") (if you would be affected by it).\n\n## History\n\n- In [0.29](/0.29 \"0.29\"), the [scroll of holy word](/Scroll_of_holy_word \"Scroll of holy word\"), the most common source of this effect, was removed.\n- Prior to [0.27](/0.27 \"0.27\"), Zin's Sanctuary caused a holy word effect.\n- Prior to [0.15](/0.15 \"0.15\"), holy word also [scared](/Cause_Fear \"Cause Fear\") targets, and the [good gods](/Good_god \"Good god\") made these scrolls more powerful for their followers.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) The power is capped at 300. TSO's holy word has power = 100. Recite's power depends on piety and [Invocations](/Invocations \"Invocations\").\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [spl-goditem.cc:1016](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.30.0/crawl-ref/source/spl-goditem.cc#L1016) (0.30.0)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [spl-goditem.cc:1036](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.30.0/crawl-ref/source/spl-goditem.cc#L1036) (0.30.0)\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html c